3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): Concurrent constraint programming is a logic-based programming paradigm, and the paper proposes an extension to handle soft constraints. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper mentions distributed soft constraint solving formalisms, and the proposed soft cc framework can also be used in distributed scenarios.
